The paper deals with document image classification and retrieval using deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which are commonly used in computer vision tasks such as object and scene analysis. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of transfer learning and feature extraction, which are common topics in machine learning and deep learning, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.DL (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper mentions the availability of a new labelled dataset, which falls under the scope of cs.MM (Multimedia).
